<br />
Green Hill Country: Hobbits for twilight -1, <br />
   hobbit farmer gets text for game<br />
Buckleberry Ferry: No skirmishes or assignments<br />
Frodo&#39;s Bedroom: Play a hobbit to draw a card, <br />
   Silinde gets text for game<br />
Moria Stairway: Damage +1 with weapons<br />
Bridge: only one<br />
Dimrill Dale: first Moria orc for twilight -2<br />
Anduin Wilderland: skips archery, needed for<br />
   endgame with weak vitality orcs<br />
Anduin Banks: adds 2 to archery for every<br />
   companion over four, hurts the super fellowship<br />
Summit of Amon Hen: draw card for burdens, none <br />
   of the other sites really offered help<br />
<br />
*Free Peoples Strategy<br />
Start with the Hobbit fellowship and bid (5-6) to go second.  This is the most important part of the deck because you must have your sites out for the deck to work properly.  Use the hobbits to heal and remove throughout the game.  Make sure to play Hobbit Farmers to pull out Green Hill Country, your site 1.  You can then use its text for the game to play hobbits for -1 twilight.  Silinde accesses the ability to draw a card when you play a hobbit from site 3.  Elrond will help you draw some more cards and keep Bilbo healed to re-circulate your Shire cards, specifically events and TaBA.  Aragorn, Boromir, and Legolas are played to help out the hobbits during the endgame.<br />
<br />
*Shadow Strategy<br />
Moria is pretty self-explanatory.  You are trying to play as many minions as you possibly can in an attempt to overwhelm your opponent.  Relics of Moria allows you to play weapons from your discard pile, in case you don&#39;t have any scavengers in play.  Goblin Swarms allows you to stack minions to save for endgame(watch out for Sleep, Caradhras).  The scouts and patrol troops are used as the archery pincushion. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=93c2396734afb2d7da9ff5ee66094933">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20721&PHPSESSID=93c2396734afb2d7da9ff5ee66094933"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20721&PHPSESSID=93c2396734afb2d7da9ff5ee66094933" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=93c2396734afb2d7da9ff5ee66094933">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
